  "prompt": "What are the best poems on women you have come across?",
  "response": "There are many powerful poems that celebrate women and explore their experiences, struggles, and strengths. Here are some notable ones:\n\n1. **\"Phenomenal Woman\" by Maya Angelou** - This poem celebrates the inner strength and beauty of women, emphasizing confidence and self-acceptance.\n\n2. **\"Still I Rise\" by Maya Angelou** - Another masterpiece by Angelou, this poem is a powerful declaration of resilience in the face of oppression, celebrating the strength of Black women.\n\n3. **\"The Woman Who Shopped\" by Alice Walker** - This poem reflects on the complexities of modern womanhood and consumerism while touching on themes of identity and autonomy.\n\n4. **\"To My Mother\" by Robert Louis Stevenson** - Though written by a man, this tender poem honors the nurturing and loving qualities of a mother, celebrating the bond between mother and child.\n\n5. **\"Aunt Jennifer's Tigers\" by Adrienne Rich** - This poem examines the constraints placed on women, using the metaphor of tigers to represent strength and freedom.\n\n6. **\"I Am Woman\" by Helen Reddy** - Though primarily known as a song, the lyrics serve as a powerful anthem for women's empowerment and strength.\n\n7. **\"The Glass Jar\" by Mary Oliver** - A reflective piece that explores the consciousness and resilience of women in their lives and relationships.\n\n8. **\"Our Grandmothers\" by Maya Angelou** - In this poem, Angelou honors the women who came before her, recognizing their struggles and sacrifices.\n\nThese poems range in style and tone, but all highlight the complexities, strength, and beauty of women. They can be powerful sources of inspiration, reflection, and empowerment.",
